{"application": "software-mentions", "version": "0.8.0", "date": "2024-10-07T11:40+0000", "md5": "4C708B7E76904FB9A8FF8DB46B311635", "mentions": [{"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Web Audio Modules", "normalizedForm": "Web Audio Modules", "offsetStart": 0, "offsetEnd": 17}, "context": "Web Audio Modules (WAM) is a standard for developing Web Audio plugins and hosts first proposed in 2015, that recently had a major update in 2021 for its 2.0 version.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 6.210803985595703e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.03307771682739258}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0020990371704101562}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 6.210803985595703e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.03307771682739258}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0020990371704101562}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "WebMidi API", "normalizedForm": "WebMidi API", "offsetStart": 10, "offsetEnd": 21}, "context": "Also, the WebMidi API, recently supported by all Major browsers, mobile and desktop ones, brings MIDI support to the browser and combined with Web Audio it became possible to control instruments using external devices (midi piano keyboard, control surfaces, pads etc.).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 6.592273712158203e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0023336410522460938}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.001362621784210205}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 6.592273712158203e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0023336410522460938}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.001362621784210205}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "WebAudio", "normalizedForm": "WebAudio", "offsetStart": 16, "offsetEnd": 24}, "context": "At the time the WebAudio API has been designed, AudioWorklets did not exist and some use cases could not be taken into account. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.46143174171447754}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.027086853981018066}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.62939453125e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.46143174171447754}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.027086853981018066}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.62939453125e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "AudioWorklet", "normalizedForm": "AudioWorklet", "offsetStart": 34, "offsetEnd": 46}, "context": "Indeed, if the DAW is built using AudioWorklet nodes for processing audio, then some parts of the code run in the high priority / audio thread. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.25841814279556274}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00013184547424316406}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.25841814279556274}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00013184547424316406}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.430511474609375e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "AudioWorklets", "normalizedForm": "AudioWorklets", "offsetStart": 48, "offsetEnd": 61}, "context": "At the time the WebAudio API has been designed, AudioWorklets did not exist and some use cases could not be taken into account. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.46143174171447754}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.027086853981018066}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.62939453125e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.46143174171447754}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.027086853981018066}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.62939453125e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Web Audio", "normalizedForm": "Web Audio", "offsetStart": 53, "offsetEnd": 62}, "context": "Web Audio Modules (WAM) is a standard for developing Web Audio plugins and hosts first proposed in 2015, that recently had a major update in 2021 for its 2.0 version.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 6.210803985595703e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.03307771682739258}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0020990371704101562}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0002982020378112793}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.03307771682739258}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0020990371704101562}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Web Audio", "normalizedForm": "Web Audio", "offsetStart": 63, "offsetEnd": 72}, "context": "Introduced in 2012 by the World Wide Web Consortium (W3C), the Web Audio API reached the \"Recommendation\" status in June 2021 (Official Standard).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0002982020378112793}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0026862025260925293}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.001668393611907959}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0002982020378112793}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.03307771682739258}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0020990371704101562}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Web Audio API", "normalizedForm": "Web Audio API", "offsetStart": 90, "offsetEnd": 103}, "context": "No need to send events from the control/GUI thread, that would have been mandatory if the Web Audio API audio node parameter management was used. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.994666576385498}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 9.21487808227539e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.994666576385498}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.007721424102783203}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.5033950805664062e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "MIDI", "normalizedForm": "MIDI", "offsetStart": 97, "offsetEnd": 101}, "context": "Also, the WebMidi API, recently supported by all Major browsers, mobile and desktop ones, brings MIDI support to the browser and combined with Web Audio it became possible to control instruments using external devices (midi piano keyboard, control surfaces, pads etc.).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 6.592273712158203e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0023336410522460938}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.001362621784210205}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 6.592273712158203e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0023336410522460938}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.001362621784210205}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "WebAssembly", "normalizedForm": "WebAssembly", "offsetStart": 102, "offsetEnd": 113}, "context": "Furthermore, it became possible to cross compile existing C/C++/Rust/Domain Specific Language code to WebAssembly, a byte code representation supported by web browsers, facilitating the port of existing DSP code to the web platform.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0003763437271118164}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.004765331745147705}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0028768181800842285}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0003763437271118164}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.004765331745147705}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0028768181800842285}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "AudioWorklets", "normalizedForm": "AudioWorklets", "offsetStart": 115, "offsetEnd": 128}, "context": "The main reason for that is to allow high performances in the case where both a DAW and plugins are implemented as AudioWorklets. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0005204081535339355}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00013506412506103516}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.46143174171447754}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.027086853981018066}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.62939453125e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "implicit", "software-name": {"rawForm": "code", "normalizedForm": "code", "offsetStart": 122, "offsetEnd": 126}, "context": "Furthermore, it became possible to cross compile existing C/C++/Rust/Domain Specific Language code to WebAssembly, a byte code representation supported by web browsers, facilitating the port of existing DSP code to the web platform.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0003763437271118164}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.004765331745147705}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0028768181800842285}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0003763437271118164}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.004765331745147705}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0028768181800842285}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "AudioWorklet", "normalizedForm": "AudioWorklet", "offsetStart": 127, "offsetEnd": 139}, "context": "Then, if a WAM plugin is associated with a given track in a DAW project (Figure 1), and if the plugin is itself built using an AudioWorklet node, it also has custom code running in the audio thread. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.12287646532058716}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 5.7816505432128906e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.430511474609375e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.25841814279556274}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00013184547424316406}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.430511474609375e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Web Audio", "normalizedForm": "Web Audio", "offsetStart": 143, "offsetEnd": 152}, "context": "Also, the WebMidi API, recently supported by all Major browsers, mobile and desktop ones, brings MIDI support to the browser and combined with Web Audio it became possible to control instruments using external devices (midi piano keyboard, control surfaces, pads etc.).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 6.592273712158203e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0023336410522460938}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.001362621784210205}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0002982020378112793}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.03307771682739258}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0020990371704101562}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "wam-studio", "normalizedForm": "wam-studio", "offsetStart": 144, "offsetEnd": 154}, "context": "Today, a WAM community Github repository proposes dozen of plugins (Figure 3: effects, instruments, utility plugins), an open source DAW called wam-studio 2 (Figure 1) is being proposed as a demonstrator for WAM plugins [4], and a real-time collaborative host called sequencer.party ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00025087594985961914}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.03488755226135254}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0007498860359191895}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00025087594985961914}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.03488755226135254}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0007498860359191895}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Web Audio API", "normalizedForm": "Web Audio API", "offsetStart": 182, "offsetEnd": 195}, "context": "The WAM framework uses an original design for handling the communication between plugins and host applications that do not rely on the low-level parameter management provided by the Web Audio API. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00018543004989624023}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.007721424102783203}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.5033950805664062e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.994666576385498}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.007721424102783203}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.5033950805664062e-06}}}], "references": [], "runtime": 11096, "id": "1c80405b616da5dfd3016238b20b5892205a8553", "metadata": {"id": "1c80405b616da5dfd3016238b20b5892205a8553"}, "original_file_path": "../../datalake/Samuel/SOFTware-Sync/downloads/xml/hal-04335580.grobid.tei.xml", "file_name": "hal-04335580.grobid.tei.xml"}